HEADWORD: passenger
<hw>pas"sen*ger</hw> <pr>(p⟦acr⟧s"s⟦ecr⟧n*j⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[OE. & F. <ets>passager</ets>. See <er>Passage</er>, and cf.
<er>Messenger</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A passer or passer-by; a
wayfarer.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A traveler by some established conveyance, as a
coach, steamboat, railroad train, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Passenger falcon</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a
migratory hawk.</cd> <au>Ainsworth.</au></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Passenger mile</ent>⟦br⟧
